Subject: [PATCH 4/4] dynamic exe: pull a shared lib's undefined libc symbols in

On a normal Linux target a shared library's undefined symbols (libembk.so
imports memcpy/vsnprintf/cosf/...) resolve at runtime from libc.so.6. EmbLink
has no runtime libc.so -- newlib is static inside every executable -- so those
symbols must be pulled INTO the app from a following archive (-lc/-lm) and
exported (-rdynamic), which is exactly what GNU ld does with
`libembk.so -lc --export-dynamic`.

Upstream tcc records the .so's undefined symbols only in dynsymtab and later
just warns ("undefined dynamic symbol vsnprintf"), so the produced app ships
WITHOUT those functions and the in-kernel dynamic loader fails to resolve them
for libembk.so (ENOEXEC). Promote each of the .so's undefined non-local
symbols into symtab_section so the subsequent archive scan satisfies it.

Gated on -rdynamic: that flag is precisely the "provide-and-export for the .so"
model this OS uses for every dynamic app, so ordinary (non-rdynamic) links are
untouched. Found while making the on-OS toolchain build EmUI apps (the GUI wall).
---
--- a/tccelf.c
+++ b/tccelf.c
@@ -2790,6 +2790,20 @@
         name = (char *) dynstr + sym->st_name;
         set_elf_sym(s1->dynsymtab_section, sym->st_value, sym->st_size,
                     sym->st_info, sym->st_other, sym->st_shndx, name);
+        /* EmbLink patch 0004: this OS has no runtime libc.so -- newlib is
+           STATIC inside every app, so a shared lib's undefined libc symbol
+           must be PULLED INTO the app from a following archive (-lc/-lm) and
+           exported (-rdynamic), exactly as GNU ld does. Upstream tcc records
+           the .so's UNDEF only in dynsymtab and later just warns, so the app
+           ships without vsnprintf/cosf/... and the in-kernel loader cannot
+           resolve them for libembk.so. Promote the .so's UNDEF into
+           symtab_section so the following archive scan satisfies it. Gated on
+           -rdynamic (the provide-and-export-for-the-.so model), leaving
+           ordinary links untouched. */
+        if (s1->rdynamic && sym->st_shndx == SHN_UNDEF)
+            set_elf_sym(symtab_section, 0, 0,
+                        ELFW(ST_INFO)(STB_GLOBAL, STT_NOTYPE), 0,
+                        SHN_UNDEF, name);
     }
 
     /* load all referenced DLLs */
